items.title: HUL gets first woman CEO - still a rarity in Indian FMCG leadership
items.description: Nair's elevation is significant for the broader consumer goods industry, a sector where women form a large chunk of the customer base but are vastly underrepresented in top leadership roles.

items.title: Tesla likely to begin first deliveries in India from August
items.description: Deliveries are expected to start from late August, a separate person familiar with the development said. Customers will be able to configure and order their Tesla EVs from next week, the person added.

items.title: Centre offers subsidy on electric trucks under PM E-Drive scheme
items.description: A dedicated provision for 1,100 e-trucks registered in Delhi has been made, with an estimated outlay of Rs 100 crore, aimed at addressing the capital’s serious air quality challenges.
